{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844316988,"sessionID":"ses_2876e587fffeh7wQuwhTosOkay","part":{"id":"prt_d7891d024001LT3q4t7caPwHgs","messageID":"msg_d7891bce0001JA4KaVON0fm0g6","sessionID":"ses_2876e587fffeh7wQuwhTosOkay","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2d628b59868547729081e064","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n5: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n6: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n7: \tcorev1lister \"k8s.io/client-go/listers/core/v1\"\n8: \n9: \truntimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n10: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/handler\"\n11: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/middleware\"\n12: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/processor\"\n13: )\n14: \n15: type Dependencies struct {\n16: \tClient    dynamic.Interface\n17: \tK8sClient kubernetes.Interface\n18: \tPodLister corev1lister.PodLister\n19: \tARLister  processor.AgentRuntimeLister\n20: \tCILister  processor.CodeInterpreterLister\n21: }\n22: \n23: func SetupRoutes(engine *gin.Engine, deps *Dependencies, health *handler.HealthHandler) {\n24: \tengine.Use(gin.Recovery())\n25: \tengine.Use(gin.Logger())\n26: \tengine.Use(middleware.RequestIDMiddleware())\n27: \n28: \tengine.GET(\"/healthz\", health.HealthzHandler)\n29: \tengine.GET(\"/readyz\", health.ReadyzHandler)\n30: \n31: \tarGroup := engine.Group(\"/api/v1/agentruntimes\")\n32: \t{\n33: \t\tarHandler := handler.NewAgentRuntimeHandler(deps.Client)\n34: \t\tarGroup.POST(\"\", arHandler.CreateAgentRuntime)\n35: \t\tarGroup.GET(\"\", arHandler.ListAgentRuntimes)\n36: \t\tarGroup.GET(\"/:name\", arHandler.GetAgentRuntime)\n37: \t\tarGroup.PUT(\"/:name\", arHandler.UpdateAgentRuntime)\n38: \t\tarGroup.DELETE(\"/:name\", arHandler.DeleteAgentRuntime)\n39: \t}\n40: \n41: \tciGroup := engine.Group(\"/api/v1/codeinterpreters\")\n42: \t{\n43: \t\tciHandler := handler.NewCodeInterpreterHandler(deps.Client)\n44: \t\tciGroup.POST(\"\", ciHandler.CreateCodeInterpreter)\n45: \t\tciGroup.GET(\"\", ciHandler.ListCodeInterpreters)\n46: \t\tciGroup.GET(\"/:name\", ciHandler.GetCodeInterpreter)\n47: \t\tciGroup.PUT(\"/:name\", ciHandler.UpdateCodeInterpreter)\n48: \t\tciGroup.DELETE(\"/:name\", ciHandler.DeleteCodeInterpreter)\n49: \t}\n50: \n51: \tsandboxGroup := engine.Group(\"/v1\")\n52: \t{\n53: \t\tsandboxHandler := handler.NewSandboxHandler(\n54: \t\t\tdeps.Client,\n55: \t\t\tdeps.K8sClient,\n56: \t\t\tdeps.PodLister,\n57: \t\t\tdeps.ARLister,\n58: \t\t\tdeps.CILister,\n59: \t\t\t\"default\",\n60: \t\t)\n61: \t\tsandboxGroup.POST(\"/agent-runtime\", sandboxHandler.HandleAgentRuntimeCreate)\n62: \t\tsandboxGroup.POST(\"/code-interpreter\", sandboxHandler.HandleCodeInterpreterCreate)\n63: \t}\n64: }\n65: \n66: type informerListerAdapter struct {\n67: \tinformer runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInformer\n68: }\n69: \n70: func (a *informerListerAdapter) AgentRuntimes(namespace string) processor.AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister {\n71: \treturn a.informer.Lister().AgentRuntimes(namespace)\n72: }\n73: \n74: type codeInterpreterListerAdapter struct {\n75: \tinformer runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInformer\n76: }\n77: \n78: func (a *codeInterpreterListerAdapter) CodeInterpreters(namespace string) processor.CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister {\n79: \treturn a.informer.Lister().CodeInterpreters(namespace)\n80: }\n\n(End of file - total 80 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport (\n\t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n\tcorev1lister \"k8s.io/client-go/listers/core/v1\"\n\n\truntimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/handler\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/middleware\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/processor\"\n)\n\ntype Dependencies struct {\n\tClient    dynamic.Interface\n\tK8sClient kubernetes.Interface\n\tPodLister corev1lister.PodLister\n\tARLister  processor.AgentRuntimeLister\n\tCILister  processor.CodeInterpreterLister","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go","time":{"start":1775844316948,"end":1775844316986}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844317011,"sessionID":"ses_2876e587fffeh7wQuwhTosOkay","part":{"id":"prt_d7891c9f7001n8ebZAOxD2auno","messageID":"msg_d7891bce0001JA4KaVON0fm0g6","sessionID":"ses_2876e587fffeh7wQuwhTosOkay","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_742803f2cd544cd880b15902","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `CreateSandboxRequest` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n18:   - Fields: `Kind`, `Name`, `Namespace` (all string)\n19:   - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n20:   - Validation rules: Kind ∈ {AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter}, Namespace non-empty, Name non-empty\n21: \n22: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `CreateSandboxResponse` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n23:   - Fields: `SessionID`, `SandboxID`, `SandboxName` (string), `EntryPoints` ([]SandboxEntryPoint)\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `SandboxEntryPoint` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n26:   - Fields: `Path`, `Protocol`, `Endpoint` (all string)\n27: \n28: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Define context keys in `pkg/workloadmanager/auth.go`\n29:   - Keys: `contextKeyUserToken`, `contextKeyServiceAccount`, `contextKeyServiceAccountName`, `contextKeyNamespace`\n30: \n31: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Define constants in `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n32:   - Constants: `DefaultSandboxTTL` (8h), `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` (15m), label/annotation keys\n33: \n34: ### Phase 2: Infrastructure Components\n35: \n36: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `sandboxCreator` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go`\n37:   - Fields: `k8sClient`, `sandboxController`, `storeClient`, `publicKey`\n38: \n39: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `createSandbox()` method for `sandboxCreator`\n40:   - Steps: register watcher → store placeholder → create CR → wait (2min) → resolve IP → update store\n41:   - Rollback on failure: delete CR + delete store entry\n42:   - Use independent 30s timeout context for rollback delete\n43: \n44: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `resolvePodIP()` method in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n45:   - Priority: sandbox name → annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` → informer cache → label selector\n46:   - Require PodRunning phase and non-empty PodIP\n47: \n48: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `buildEntryPoints()` function in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n49:   - Input: podIP, []TargetPort\n50:   - Output: []SandboxEntryPoint with format `host:port`\n51: \n52: ### Phase 3: Workload Builders\n53: \n54: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `buildSandboxObject()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n55:   - Input: *AgentRuntime, sessionID\n56:   - Name format: `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`\n57:   - Set labels: session-id, workload-name, sandbox-name, managed-by\n58:   - Set annotations: idle-timeout\n59:   - Copy podTemplate from runtime.Spec.Template\n60:   - Set replicas=1, lifecycle.shutdownTime=now+MaxSessionDuration\n61: \n62: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `buildSandboxClaimObject()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n63:   - For CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize > 0\n64:   - Minimal metadata, no full PodSpec\n65:   - APIVersion: `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, Kind: `SandboxClaim`\n66: \n67: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement AuthMode injection for CodeInterpreter\n68:   - If AuthMode=picod and publicKey available: inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var\n69:   - Support optional fields: Command, Args, Environment, Resources, RuntimeClassName, ImagePullPolicy, ImagePullSecrets\n70: \n71: ### Phase 4: HTTP Handlers\n72: \n73: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `handleAgentRuntimeCreate()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/agent_runtime.go`\n74:   - Parse JSON → set Kind=AgentRuntime → Validate()\n75:   - Get AgentRuntime from informer lister\n76:   - Check podTemplate non-nil\n77:   - Call createSandbox()\n78:   - Return CreateSandboxResponse (200) or error\n79: \n80: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `handleCodeInterpreterCreate()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/code_interpreter.go`\n81:   - Similar to AgentRuntime but:\n82:   - Kind=CodeInterpreter\n83:   - Support WarmPoolSize > 0 → buildSandboxClaimObject()\n84:   - Support AuthMode (picod/none)\n85:   - Default ports: [{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\", PathPrefix: \"/\"}] if spec.Ports empty\n86: \n87: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Register routes in `pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go`\n88:   - POST /v1/agent-runtime → handleAgentRuntimeCreate\n89:   - DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId → handleDeleteSandbox\n90:   - POST /v1/code-interpreter → handleCodeInterpreterCreate\n91:   - DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId → handleDeleteSandbox\n92: \n93: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `handleDeleteSandbox()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/agent_runtime.go`\n94:   - Load session from store by sessionId\n95:   - NotFound → 404 with message `Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted`\n96:   - Delete SandboxClaim if Kind=SandboxClaim, else delete Sandbox\n97:   - API NotFound on delete → treat as success\n98:   - DeleteSandboxBySessionID from store\n99:   - Return 200 `{\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}`\n100: \n101: ### Phase 5: Error Handling\n102: \n103: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Define error constants in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go` or `pkg/workloadmanager/response/response.go`\n104:   - ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound, ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound, ErrTemplateMissing, ErrPublicKeyMissing\n105: \n106: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement error mapping in handlers\n107:   - JSON bind失败 → 400 `Invalid request body`\n108:   - Validate 失败 → 400 `<field> is required`\n109:   - Template missing → 400 with `pod template` in message\n110:   - NotFound from informer → 404 `agent runtime not found` / `code interpreter not found`\n111:   - Auth失败 → 401 from authMiddleware\n112:   - Timeout/internal → 500 `internal server error`\n113: \n114: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement rollback strategy in `createSandbox()`\n115:   - CR 创建前失败: delete store placeholder\n116:   - CR 创建后超时: delete CR (30s timeout) + delete store\n117:   - Pod IP 解析失败: delete CR + delete store\n118:   - Store 更新失败: log warning, CR left for GC\n119: \n120: ### Phase 6: Integration\n121: \n122: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Integrate with `client-go` typed clients\n123:   - Use `AgentRuntimeInterface` and `CodeInterpreterInterface` for reading templates\n124:   - Use informers + listers for cached reads\n125: \n126: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Integrate with dynamic client\n127:   - Create Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs using `dynamic.Interface`\n128:   - GVR: `SandboxGVR`, `SandboxClaimGVR`\n129: \n130: - [ ] **TASK-052**: Integrate with SandboxReconciler\n131:   - Call `WatchSandboxOnce(ns, name)` before CR creation\n132:   - Wait on channel with 2min timeout\n133:   - Receive notification when status=running\n134: \n135: - [ ] **TASK-053**: Integrate with Store\n136:   - StoreSandbox() with placeholder before CR create\n137:   - UpdateSandbox() with full info after IP resolution\n138:   - DeleteSandboxBySessionID() on rollback or delete\n139: \n140: - [ ] **TASK-054**: Integrate with authMiddleware\n141:   - When EnableAuth=true: use per-user dynamic client from `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient`\n142:   - Cache key: `<namespace>:<serviceAccountName>`\n143: \n144: ### Phase 7: Testing (TDD)\n145: \n146: #### Unit Tests\n147: \n148: - [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestCreateSandboxRequest_Validate` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers_test.go`\n149:   - Valid request → no error\n150:   - Empty name → error contains `name is required`\n151:   - Empty namespace → error contains `namespace is required`\n152:   - Invalid kind → error contains `kind is required`\n153: \n154: - [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_Success` (TestCase-WM-001)\n155:   - Given: valid AgentRuntime in informer cache\n156:   - When: POST /v1/agent-runtime with valid JSON\n157:   - Then: 200, response contains sessionId and entryPoints\n158:   - Use fake clientset + mock store + mock SandboxReconciler\n159: \n160: - [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_Idempotent` (TestCase-WM-002)\n161:   - Given: two consecutive requests with same name\n162:   - When: first creation succeeds\n163:   - Then: second returns same sessionId\n164: \n165: - [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_MissingPodTemplate` (TestCase-WM-003)\n166:   - Given: AgentRuntime with spec.podTemplate=nil\n167:   - When: POST /v1/agent-runtime\n168:   - Then: 400, message contains `pod template`\n169: \n170: - [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_WarmPool`\n171:   - Given: CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize > 0\n172:   - When: POST /v1/code-interpreter\n173:   - Then: creates SandboxClaim, response Kind=SandboxClaim\n174: \n175: - [ ] **TEST-006**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_DefaultPorts`\n176:   - Given: CodeInterpreter with empty spec.Ports\n177:   - When: creation succeeds\n178:   - Then: entryPoints contains default 8080/HTTP\n179: \n180: - [ ] **TEST-007**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_AuthModePicoD`\n181:   - Given: AuthMode=picod and publicKey available\n182:   - When: sandbox created\n183:   - Then: PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY env var injected\n184: \n185: - [ ] **TEST-008**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_AuthModeNone`\n186:   - Given: AuthMode=none\n187:   - When: sandbox created\n188:   - Then: no PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY env var\n189: \n190: - [ ] **TEST-009**: `TestCreateSandbox_Timeout`\n191:   - Given: no running notification within 2min\n192:   - When: createSandbox() waits\n193:   - Then: error `sandbox creation timed out`, CR deleted, store entry deleted\n194: \n195: - [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestCreateSandbox_RollbackOnIPResolutionFailure`\n196:   - Given: pod IP resolution fails\n197:   - When: createSandbox() attempts to resolve\n198:   - Then: CR deleted, store entry deleted, error returned\n199: \n200: - [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestResolvePodIP_FromAnnotation`\n201:   - Given: Sandbox with annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name`\n202:   - When: resolvePodIP() called\n203:   - Then: uses annotated pod name\n204: \n205: - [ ] **TEST-012**: `TestResolvePodIP_FromOwnerReference`\n206:   - Given: pods listed by label, one has owner reference Kind=Sandbox\n207:   - When: resolvePodIP() called\n208:   - Then: selects pod with matching owner reference\n209: \n210: - [ ] **TEST-013**: `TestResolvePodIP_PodNotRunning`\n211:   - Given: pod in Pending/Failed phase\n212:   - When: resolvePodIP() called\n213:   - Then: error indicating pod not running\n214: \n215: - [ ] **TEST-014**: `TestBuildSandboxObject_LabelsAndAnnotations`\n216:   - Given: AgentRuntime with sessionTimeout\n217:   - When: buildSandboxObject() called\n218:   - Then: labels and annotations set correctly\n219: \n220: - [ ] **TEST-015**: `TestBuildSandboxClaimObject_MinimalMetadata`\n221:   - Given: CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize > 0\n222:   - When: buildSandboxClaimObject() called\n223:   - Then: minimal metadata, no PodSpec\n224: \n225: - [ ] **TEST-016**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_Success`\n226:   - Given: session exists in store\n227:   - When: DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId\n228:   - Then: 200, CR deleted, store entry deleted\n229: \n230: - [ ] **TEST-017**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_NotFound` (Spec requirement)\n231:   - Given: no session key in store\n232:   - When: DELETE invoked\n233:   - Then: 404, message contains session id\n234: \n235: #### Test Infrastructure\n236: \n237: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `testEnv` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go`\n238:   - Fields: k8sClient, reconciler, store, server, redis (miniredis), fakeClient, dynamicClient\n239: \n240: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Implement `newTestEnv(t *testing.T)` function\n241:   - Start miniredis\n242:   - Create fake clientset with registered AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter\n243:   - Create fake dynamic client\n244:   - Initialize K8sClient, SandboxReconciler, Store\n245:   - Build Server (auth/TLS disabled)\n246: \n247: - [ ] **TEST-022**: Create mock implementations\n248:   - MockWorkloadManager interface\n249:   - Mock SandboxReconciler.WatchSandboxOnce returning controllable channel\n250: \n251: #### Integration Tests\n252: \n253: - [ ] **TEST-030**: `TestE2E_CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox`\n254:   - Deploy AgentCube (Helm install to Kind cluster)\n255:   - Create ServiceAccount and get token\n256:   - POST /v1/agent-runtime\n257:   - Verify response contains sessionId and entryPoints\n258:   - Access sandbox via entryPoint to verify connectivity\n259:   - DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId to cleanup\n260: \n261: - [ ] **TEST-031**: E2E fixture `echo_agent.yaml`\n262:   - Simple echo server AgentRuntime definition\n263: \n264: #### Coverage Verification\n265: \n266: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Run coverage check\n267:   - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n268:   - Verify test code / business code ratio > 0.4\n269:   - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go\n270: \n271: ### Phase 8: Documentation\n272: \n273: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add API examples to handler doc comments\n274:   - Example request/response for POST /v1/agent-runtime\n275:   - Example request/response for POST /v1/code-interpreter\n276: \n277: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Document error scenarios in handler doc comments\n278:   - List all HTTP status codes and conditions\n279: \n280: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Update pkg/workloadmanager/README.md\n281:   - Architecture diagram\n282:   - Component interaction flow\n283:   - Configuration options\n284: \n285: ## Acceptance Criteria\n286: \n287: - [ ] All handlers implemented and registered\n288: - [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)\n289: - [ ] Test coverage ratio > 0.4\n290: - [ ] Error handling covers all spec-defined scenarios\n291: - [ ] Rollback strategy verified by tests\n292: - [ ] Integration with client-go, informers, dynamic client, Store, SandboxReconciler complete\n293: - [ ] Auth mode (EnableAuth) tested with per-user client cache\n294: - [ ] WarmPool support for CodeInterpreter verified\n295: - [ ] Timeout (2min) and rollback (30s) enforced\n296: - [ ] Pod IP resolution covers all paths (annotation, owner reference, label selector)\n297: \n298: ## Dependencies\n299: \n300: - **Completed**: ST-1 (CRD schemas), ST-2 (HTTP framework, auth middleware, informers)\n301: - **Required**: client-go typed clients, informers, listers operational\n302: - **Required**: SandboxReconciler operational (from controller package)\n303: - **Required**: Store interface (Redis-backed) operational\n\n(End of file - total 303 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `CreateSandboxRequest` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n  - Fields: `Kind`, `Name`, `Namespace` (all string)\n  - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n  - Validation rules: Kind ∈ {AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter}, Namespace non-empty, Name non-empty","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775844316943,"end":1775844317006}}}}
