{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844395917,"sessionID":"ses_2876e587fffeh7wQuwhTosOkay","part":{"id":"prt_d789223ea001TlUyf2CUCcPlR9","messageID":"msg_d789215e5001jpDe3tr0XJ6QUL","sessionID":"ses_2876e587fffeh7wQuwhTosOkay","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_2d687b4cdaa24a34810c806f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-006-sandbox-deletion-lifecycle/tasks.md","content":"# AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `DeleteSandboxResponse` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox_types.go`\n  - Field: `Message` (string)\n  - JSON tag: `{\"message\":\"...\"}`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `SandboxCleanupReason` type and constants in `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox_types.go`\n  - Type: `type SandboxCleanupReason string`\n  - Constants: `CleanupReasonManual`, `CleanupReasonIdleTimeout`, `CleanupReasonExpired`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `CleanupAuditEntry` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox_types.go`\n  - Fields: `SessionID`, `SandboxID`, `Namespace` (string), `Reason` (SandboxCleanupReason), `DeletedAt` (time.Time), `Success` (bool), `ErrorMessage` (string, omitempty)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-004**: Define lifecycle constants in `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n  - Constants: `DefaultSandboxTTL` (8h), `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` (15m), `GCInterval` (15s), `GCSingleTickTimeout` (2m), `DeleteTimeout` (30s)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-005**: Define label/annotation keys in `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n  - Keys: `SessionIDLabelKey`, `WorkloadNameLabelKey`, `SandboxNameLabelKey`, `LastActivityAnnotationKey`, `IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey`, `ManagedByLabel`\n\n### Phase 2: GarbageCollector Infrastructure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `garbageCollector` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n  - Fields: `k8sClient` (*K8sClient), `storeClient` (store.Store), `interval` (time.Duration), `ctx` (context.Context), `cancel` (context.CancelFunc)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `newGarbageCollector()` constructor\n  - Parameters: k8sClient, storeClient, interval\n  - Creates context with context.WithCancel\n  - Returns initialized *garbageCollector\n\n- [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `Start()` method for GarbageCollector\n  - Launches `gcLoop()` as goroutine\n  - Non-blocking\n\n- [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `Stop()` method for GarbageCollector\n  - Calls cancel() to signal shutdown\n  - Graceful termination\n\n- [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `gcLoop()` method\n  - Creates ticker with gc.interval\n  - Select on ctx.Done() and ticker.C\n  - Calls `tick()` on each tick\n  - Logs start/stop messages\n\n- [ ] **TASK-015**: Implement `tick()` method\n  - Creates context with GCSingleTickTimeout\n  - Calculates idleThreshold (now - DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout) and expiredThreshold (now)\n  - Calls ListInactiveSandboxes with limit 16\n  - Calls ListExpiredSandboxes with limit 16\n  - For each sandbox, calls `deleteSandbox()` with appropriate reason\n\n- [ ] **TASK-016**: Implement `deleteSandbox()` method\n  - Creates CleanupAuditEntry\n  - Determines GVR based on Kind (SandboxClaim vs Sandbox)\n  - Creates delete context with DeleteTimeout\n  - Calls dynamicClient.Delete\n  - Treats K8s NotFound as success\n  - Calls DeleteSandboxBySessionID on success\n  - Logs warning on Store delete failure (doesn't fail request)\n  - Calls `recordAudit()`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-017**: Implement `recordAudit()` method\n  - Logs audit entry as info level\n  - Structured logging with entry fields\n\n### Phase 3: Delete Handler\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `HandleDeleteSandbox()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox.go`\n  - Extract sessionId from gin.Context.Param(\"sessionId\")\n  - Validate sessionId non-empty → 400 if empty\n  - Call store.GetSandboxBySessionID\n  - Handle ErrNotFound → 404 with message containing session id\n  - Handle other store errors → 500\n  - Determine GVR based on SandboxInfo.Kind\n  - Call dynamicClient.Delete with DeleteTimeout\n  - Treat K8s NotFound as success\n  - Call DeleteSandboxBySessionID (log warning on failure)\n  - Return 200 with DeleteSandboxResponse\n\n- [ ] **TASK-021**: Register DELETE routes in `pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go`\n  - DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId → HandleDeleteSandbox\n  - DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId → HandleDeleteSandbox\n\n### Phase 4: Server Integration\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Add `garbageCollector` field to `Server` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-031**: Initialize GarbageCollector in `NewServer()`\n  - Call `newGarbageCollector(client, store.Storage(), GCInterval)`\n  - Assign to server.garbageCollector\n\n- [ ] **TASK-032**: Start GarbageCollector in `Run()` method\n  - Call `s.garbageCollector.Start()` before HTTP server starts\n\n- [ ] **TASK-033**: Stop GarbageCollector in `Shutdown()` method\n  - Call `s.garbageCollector.Stop()` before HTTP shutdown\n\n### Phase 5: Error Handling\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement error mapping in handler\n  - sessionId empty → 400 `sessionId is required`\n  - Store NotFound → 404 `Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted`\n  - Store other error → 500 `internal server error`\n  - K8s API error (non-NotFound) → 500 `internal server error`\n  - K8s NotFound → treat as success (continue to delete store record)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement rollback strategy\n  - K8s delete fails (non-NotFound): don't delete store record, return 500\n  - K8s delete succeeds but Store delete fails: log warning, don't return error\n  - K8s returns NotFound: continue to delete store record, return 200\n\n### Phase 6: Testing (TDD)\n\n#### Unit Tests - Handler\n\n- [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_Success` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_test.go`\n  - Given: session exists in store and K8s\n  - When: DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId\n  - Then: 200, response contains \"Sandbox deleted successfully\"\n  - Verify: store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID called\n\n- [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_NotFound` (TestCase-WM-004)\n  - Given: session not in store\n  - When: DELETE invoked\n  - Then: 404, message contains session id and \"not found\"\n\n- [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_KubernetesNotFound`\n  - Given: session in store but not in K8s\n  - When: DELETE invoked\n  - Then: 200 (K8s NotFound treated as success), store record deleted\n\n- [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_SandboxClaim`\n  - Given: Kind=SandboxClaim in store\n  - When: DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId\n  - Then: 200, SandboxClaim deleted (not Sandbox)\n\n- [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_EmptySessionId`\n  - Given: sessionId is empty string\n  - When: DELETE invoked\n  - Then: 400, message contains \"sessionId is required\"\n\n- [ ] **TEST-006**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_StoreError`\n  - Given: store returns non-NotFound error\n  - When: DELETE invoked\n  - Then: 500, message \"internal server error\"\n\n#### Unit Tests - GarbageCollector\n\n- [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_IdleSandboxes` in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n  - Given: ListInactiveSandboxes returns sandbox\n  - When: tick() called\n  - Then: sandbox deleted from K8s and store\n\n- [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_ExpiredSandboxes`\n  - Given: ListExpiredSandboxes returns sandbox\n  - When: tick() called\n  - Then: sandbox deleted from K8s and store\n\n- [ ] **TEST-012**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_KubernetesNotFound`\n  - Given: sandbox in store but not in K8s\n  - When: tick() called\n  - Then: store record still deleted, no error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-013**: `TestGarbageCollector_StartStop`\n  - Given: initialized GC\n  - When: Start() then Stop() called\n  - Then: gcLoop exits cleanly (no panic, context cancelled)\n\n- [ ] **TEST-014**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_BothLists`\n  - Given: both idle and expired sandboxes returned\n  - When: tick() called\n  - Then: all sandboxes processed, no duplicates if overlap\n\n- [ ] **TEST-015**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_ListInactiveError`\n  - Given: ListInactiveSandboxes returns error\n  - When: tick() called\n  - Then: error logged, continues to ListExpiredSandboxes\n\n- [ ] **TEST-016**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_ListExpiredError`\n  - Given: ListExpiredSandboxes returns error\n  - When: tick() called\n  - Then: error logged, doesn't crash\n\n#### Test Infrastructure\n\n- [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `buildUnstructuredSandbox()` helper in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n  - Returns *unstructured.Unstructured with apiVersion, kind, metadata\n  - Sets required labels\n\n- [ ] **TEST-021**: Create `buildUnstructuredSandboxClaim()` helper\n  - Similar to above but for SandboxClaim\n\n- [ ] **TEST-022**: Create mock store interface\n  - Mock Store with methods: GetSandboxBySessionID, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListInactiveSandboxes, ListExpiredSandboxes\n\n#### Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-030**: `TestE2E_DeleteSandbox` in `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n  - Deploy AgentCube (Helm to Kind)\n  - Create sandbox via POST /v1/agent-runtime\n  - Verify sandbox accessible\n  - DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId\n  - Verify 200 response\n  - Verify sandbox deleted (GET should 404)\n\n- [ ] **TEST-031**: `TestE2E_GarbageCollector_IdleTimeout`\n  - Create sandbox\n  - Wait for idle timeout (15m + GCInterval)\n  - Verify sandbox auto-deleted by GC\n\n- [ ] **TEST-032**: `TestE2E_GarbageCollector_Expired`\n  - Create sandbox with short TTL (override for test)\n  - Wait for expiration\n  - Verify sandbox auto-deleted by GC\n\n#### Coverage Verification\n\n- [ ] **TEST-040**: Run coverage check\n  - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n  - Verify test code / business code ratio > 0.4\n  - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go\n\n### Phase 7: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-001**: Add API examples to handler doc comments\n  - Example DELETE request/response for AgentRuntime\n  - Example DELETE request/response for CodeInterpreter\n\n- [ ] **DOC-002**: Document error scenarios in handler doc comments\n  - List all HTTP status codes and conditions\n  - Explain K8s NotFound treated as success\n\n- [ ] **DOC-003**: Document GarbageCollector behavior\n  - GC interval, batch size, timeout values\n  - Cleanup reasons (manual/idle_timeout/expired)\n  - Audit logging\n\n- [ ] **DOC-004**: Add configuration options to README\n  - Environment variables for GC_INTERVAL, SANDBOX_TTL, IDLE_TIMEOUT\n  - Default values and recommended ranges\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Delete handler implemented for both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n- [ ] GarbageCollector implemented with idle and expired cleanup\n- [ ] All handlers and GC routes registered\n- [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)\n- [ ] Test coverage ratio > 0.4\n- [ ] Error handling covers all spec-defined scenarios\n- [ ] K8s NotFound treated as success (verified by tests)\n- [ ] Store delete failures logged as warnings (not returned to client)\n- [ ] GC runs every 15s with 2m tick timeout\n- [ ] GC batch size 16 for both idle and expired lists\n- [ ] Audit logging for all GC deletions\n- [ ] Server properly starts/stops GC lifecycle\n- [ ] Integration with Store (Get/Delete/List) verified\n- [ ] Integration with dynamic client (Delete) verified\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- **Completed**: ST-1 (CRD schemas), ST-2 (HTTP framework, auth middleware, informers)\n- **Required**: Store interface operational (GetSandboxBySessionID, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListInactiveSandboxes, ListExpiredSandboxes)\n- **Required**: dynamic client configured for Sandbox/SandboxClaim GVR\n- **Required**: SandboxReconciler operational (for watcher cleanup on delete)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go\">\nERROR [67:27] undefined: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInformer\nERROR [75:27] undefined: runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInformer\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":66,"character":26},"end":{"line":66,"character":46}},"severity":1,"code":"UndeclaredImportedName","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#UndeclaredImportedName"},"source":"compiler","message":"undefined: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInformer"},{"range":{"start":{"line":74,"character":26},"end":{"line":74,"character":49}},"severity":1,"code":"UndeclaredImportedName","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#UndeclaredImportedName"},"source":"compiler","message":"undefined: runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInformer"}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-006-sandbox-deletion-lifecycle/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-006-sandbox-deletion-lifecycle/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775844395904,"end":1775844395914}}}}
